本論文永久網址:      Twitter研究生:歐皖蘭研究生(外文):Wan-lan Ou論文名稱:文化景觀保存與鄉村社區發展之研究－以臺南縣後壁鄉菁寮聚落為例論文名稱(外文):A Case Study on the Preservation of Cultural Landscapes and  Commnity Development in Ching-Liao Village, Tainan County指導教授:薛怡珍學位類別:碩士校院名稱:國立臺南大學系所名稱:生態旅遊研究所碩士班學門:民生學門學類:觀光休閒學類論文出版年:2010畢業學年度:98語文別:中文論文頁數:292中文關鍵詞:農村生活博物館、社區參與、文化景觀、菁寮聚落外文關鍵詞:community participation、cultural landscape、Ching-Liao village、rural eco-museum相關次數:

被引用:7點閱:1882評分:下載:381書目收藏:8



菁寮聚落是嘉南平原典型的稻作農村聚落，迄今仍保有傳統的三合院建築、古蹟、老街、傳統商業，以及閒置的農田水利設施和穀倉等農村意象，充分展現在時空脈絡中所形塑的農村文化景觀。但可能長期受到工業化經濟衝擊，菁寮聚落日漸凋蔽，人力嚴重外流，農村文化資產已經面臨是否應該被保存的危機。今日菁寮聚落的居民自發性組成「無米樂農村再生促進會」，並將聚落發展願景定位為「農村生活博物館」，希望藉此促進居民對文化的認同感，進而提升農村的生活環境品質。同時在以不影響居民日常生活為前題，導入農事或歷史場景遊憩體驗，以促進城鄉文化交流和農村文化保存之目標。目前來自政府所投入社區的資源甚多，舉凡如文建會的「區域型文化資產環境保存與活化計畫」和水保局「農村再生建設先期規劃」等計畫的支持，加上專業輔導團隊的進駐，希望為菁寮聚落重新找回昔日的繁華景象。本研究以行動研究進行參與觀察和居民深度訪談，希望瞭解政府在當地所導（投）入的「區域型文化資產環境保存與活化計畫」之文化景觀保存相關行動，對菁寮聚落所造成的影響。同時觀察居民參與情形，以及政府、專業團隊的執行機制對其文化景觀保存效益之影響，並分析當地居民對相關計畫執行機制的看法，藉此釐清影響當地推動農村文化景觀保存之因素。本研究以將近一年半的時間實際進行參與式的田野調查，結果發現利用政策推動文化保存行動對於建立居民保存當地文化資產的觀念確實有著啟發的作用，但由於政策的推動多是以「由上而下」和專家執行之機制進行，再加上諸多單位計畫多頭馬車同時進行、計畫執行時程之壓力，以及研究區的行政區隔等問題，在尚未釐清地方歷史脈絡，和居民認知、培力、參與機制均未成熟之狀況下，已嚴重影響當地整體文化景觀保存的利基與效益。研究結果發現建立地方完整的歷史資料，整合政策與政府的資源，專業團隊的執行力與投入，擬訂在地化的保存計畫，和推動居民參與的強度才是影響地區文化景觀與社區永續發展的最重要因素。

The Ching-Liao village in the Chianan plain is one typical agricultural village in Taiwan. Up to now, it still preserves many agriculture images, such as san-ho-yuan, historic remains, old-fashioned streets, traditional commerce, farmland-irrigating facilities and the granary. These historical elements feature their rural cultural landscapes. But possibly for a long time with the economic impacts of industrialization, the village’s manpower has gradually decimated and flowed out seriously. The village is in the face of a preservation crisis of losing its rural cultural assets. By now, with a vision of building a “Rural Eco-Museum”, local residents are self-motivated to form an organization called “Let it be” for rural regeneration. They hope to cultivate local residents’ cultural identity and to improve their rural living environment. In addition to that, by rebuilding conventional rural scenes for the tourists to experience, the residents and visitors will interactive in the natural scenario, which will lead to the vision of the city-country interaction and rural cultural preservation.Currently, the village gains many government’s funds in reconstructing rural landscape, such as “the Plan for the Preservation of cultural Assets and Renovation Reusing in Area” from the Council for Cultural Affairs of Taiwan and “the Plan of Rural Regeneration” from the Soil and Water Conservation Bureau in Southern Regions. Besides, some professional teams are researching here as well. All this effort hopes to rehabilitate the village returning its prosperous.In this study, action research carried out participant observation and in-depth interviews with residents, with the aim of understanding how “the Plan for the Preservation of cultural Assets and Renovation Reusing in Area”, as the main axis of the preservation of cultural landscape related actions, affects the Ching-Liao village. In the meanwhile, this study not only investigates the situation that residents get involved and the impact of the program efficiency on the execution mechanism in government agencies and professional groups, but also compares with the residents’ impression of the program execution to clarify the impact factor on the local promotion of the cultural landscape preservation.According to the one and a half year-long fieldwork in the study site, I found that the policy-promoted cultural preservation action surely inspires the residents’ conservation concepts. However, in the context of yet being clarified local history and the scenario of insufficient cognition, and participation for residents, the hydra-headed policy that is implemented by a top-down driven and expert-executed mechanism and the problem of unclear administrative regions in the study area seriously affect the benefits of cultural landscape preservation. By the case study of Ching-Liao village, this study suggests that the establishment of the complete local history investigation, policy integration and support, executive force and involvement of professional groups, draft of the site-specific conservation programs, and participation of residents are the important factors on affecting the sustainable development of cultural landscapes in this community

